Meet <b>Paige</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Paige lives at <a href='/home/?user=cuttiepie18957'>52559 Castle Hill</a> in Westridge, where she has a sweeping view of Millsberry and the surrounding countryside.  Paige moved to Millsberry on October 17, 2004, and she's been enjoying the cozy, small-town atmosphere here ever since.<br><br>In spite of her calm appearance and friendly personality, Paige is a fierce competitor, and she has the trophies to prove it.  Though she excels at more athletic games like <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=140">Sink the Three</a> and <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=13">Hop-N-Drop</a>, Paige also enjoys challenging herself with intellectual games, such as <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=12">Solver</a>.  Her competitive nature, combined with a desire to always meet the goals that she has set for herself, makes Paige a great student.  She's very smart, and really likes to read and study, especially if the subject is math.<br><br>In addition to flexing her mathematical muscles, Paige also has a creative side.  For example, she is a very passionate painter, who loves to spend long afternoons in her studio, covering canvases with bold streaks of pink, orange, and violet.  Her vibrant, expressive paintings are often inspired by the music she listens to while painting.  Paige transforms the detailed lines of jazz, the forceful beats of rap, and the lilting melodies of country into colorful patterns and shapes.<br><br>Paige recently began using her creativity in a new way - by making music at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio/">Millsberry Recording Studio</a>.  Her excitement for painting has carried over into her musical pursuits, and it really shines through in her tracks.  Paige's enthusiasm for the creative process has had a great impact on her many listeners, who have taken her song to the top of the Cinnamon Toast Crunch Top Ten chart.<br><br>When she's not busy working on her art, Paige can usually be found hanging out with her friends at a mall or playing hide-and-seek with them at a playground.  To really unwind, Paige likes spending a quiet afternoon at her best friend's house, either doing homework or just having a long chat.         <br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Paige, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
